main event: Observation of a spherical object with a fiery trail, traveling from northwest to southeast in Pori, Finland on September 20, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed for several seconds.
The object was described as spherical in shape with a fiery trail.
The object made no sound as it traveled.
A Finnish Academy Professor evaluated the object as a meteor.
The case was classified as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation' by Project Blue Book.
sighted object: A spherical object with a fiery trail
